','','','2014-06-24 06:15:12','2014-06-24 06:15:12','',0,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/classes/wp_automatic_updater/',0,'wp-parser-class','',0),(959,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','','WP_Automatic_Updater::is_disabled','Whether the entire automatic updater is disabled.','publish','open','open','','wp_automatic_updater-is_disabled','','','2014-06-24 06:15:12','2014-06-24 06:15:12','',958,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/classes/wp_automatic_updater/is_disabled/',0,'wp-parser-method','',0),(960,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','<p>There are more fine-grained filters and controls for selective disabling.\nThis filter parallels the AUTOMATIC_UPDATER_DISABLED constant in name.</p>\n<p>This also disables update notification emails. That may change in the future.</p>','\'automatic_updater_disabled\'','Filter whether to entirely disable background updates.','publish','open','open','','automatic_updater_disabled','','','2014-06-24 06:15:12','2014-06-24 06:15:12','',959,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/hooks/automatic_updater_disabled/',0,'wp-parser-hook','',0),(961,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','<p>Checks for Subversion, Git, Mercurial, and Bazaar. It recursively looks up the\nfilesystem to the top of the drive, erring on the side of detecting a VCS\ncheckout somewhere.</p>\n<p>ABSPATH is always checked in addition to whatever $context is (which may be the\nwp-content directory, for example). The underlying assumption is that if you are\nusing version control <em>anywhere</em>, then you should be making decisions for\nhow things get updated.</p>','WP_Automatic_Updater::is_vcs_checkout','Check for version control checkouts.','publish','open','open','','wp_automatic_updater-is_vcs_checkout','','','2014-06-24 06:15:12','2014-06-24 06:15:12','',958,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/classes/wp_automatic_updater/is_vcs_checkout/',0,'wp-parser-method','',0),(962,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','','\'automatic_updates_is_vcs_checkout\'','Filter whether the automatic updater should consider a filesystem\nlocation to be potentially managed by a version control system.','publish','open','open','','automatic_updates_is_vcs_checkout','','','2014-06-24 06:15:12','2014-06-24 06:15:12','',961,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/hooks/automatic_updates_is_vcs_checkout/',0,'wp-parser-hook','',0),(963,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','','WP_Automatic_Updater::should_update','Tests to see if we can and should update a specific item.','publish','open','open','','wp_automatic_updater-should_update','','','2014-06-24 06:15:12','2014-06-24 06:15:12','',958,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/classes/wp_automatic_updater/should_update/',0,'wp-parser-method','',0),(964,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','<p>The dynamic portion of the hook name, $type, refers to the type of update\nbeing checked. Can be \'core\', \'theme\', \'plugin\', or \'translation\'.</p>\n<p>Generally speaking, plugins, themes, and major core versions are not updated\nby default, while translations and minor and development versions for core\nare updated by default.</p>\n<p>See the allow_dev_auto_core_updates, allow_minor_auto_core_updates, and\nallow_major_auto_core_updates filters for a more straightforward way to\nadjust core updates.</p>','\'auto_update_\' . $type','Filter whether to automatically update core, a plugin, a theme, or a language.','publish','open','open','','auto_update_-type','','','2014-06-24 06:15:12','2014-06-24 06:15:12','',963,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/hooks/auto_update_-type/',0,'wp-parser-hook','',0),(965,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','','WP_Automatic_Updater::send_core_update_notification_email','Notifies an administrator of a core update.','publish','open','open','','wp_automatic_updater-send_core_update_notification_email','','','2014-06-24 06:15:12','2014-06-24 06:15:12','',958,'http://developer.word