ons/install_plugins_favorites_form/',0,'wp-parser-function','',0),(2669,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:50','2014-06-24 06:04:50','','display_plugins_table','Display plugin content based on plugin list.','publish','open','open','','display_plugins_table','','','2014-06-24 06:04:50','2014-06-24 06:04:50','',0,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/functions/display_plugins_table/',0,'wp-parser-function','',0),(2670,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:50','2014-06-24 06:04:50','','install_plugin_install_status','Determine the status we can perform on a plugin.','publish','open','open','','install_plugin_install_status','','','2014-06-24 06:17:44','2014-06-24 06:17:44','',0,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/functions/install_plugin_install_status/',0,'wp-parser-function','',0),(2671,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','','install_plugin_information','Display plugin information in dialog box form.','publish','open','open','','install_plugin_information','','','2014-06-24 06:17:53','2014-06-24 06:17:53','',0,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/functions/install_plugin_information/',0,'wp-parser-function','',0),(2672,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','<p>The metadata of the plugin\'s data searches for the following in the plugin\'s\nheader. All plugin data must be on its own line. For plugin description, it\nmust not have any newlines or only parts of the description will be displayed\nand the same goes for the plugin data. The below is formatted for printing.</p>\n<pre><code>/*\nPlugin Name: Name of Plugin\nPlugin URI: Link to plugin information\nDescription: Plugin Description\nAuthor: Plugin author\'s name\nAuthor URI: Link to the author\'s web site\nVersion: Must be set in the plugin for WordPress 2.3+\nText Domain: Optional. Unique identifier, should be same as the one used in\n    plugin_text_domain()\nDomain Path: Optional. Only useful if the translations are located in a\n    folder above the plugin\'s base path. For example, if .mo files are\n    located in the locale folder then Domain Path will be \"/locale/\" and\n    must have the first slash. Defaults to the base folder the plugin is\n    located in.\nNetwork: Optional. Specify \"Network: true\" to require that a plugin is activated\n    across all sites in an installation. This will prevent a plugin from being\n    activated on a single site when Multisite is enabled.\n * / # Remove the space to close comment\n</code></pre>\n<p>Plugin data returned array contains the following:</p>\n<pre><code>\'Name\' - Name of the plugin, must be unique.\n\'Title\' - Title of the plugin and the link to the plugin\'s web site.\n\'Description\' - Description of what the plugin does and/or notes\nfrom the author.\n\'Author\' - The author\'s name\n\'AuthorURI\' - The authors web site address.\n\'Version\' - The plugin version number.\n\'PluginURI\' - Plugin web site address.\n\'TextDomain\' - Plugin\'s text domain for localization.\n\'DomainPath\' - Plugin\'s relative directory path to .mo files.\n\'Network\' - Boolean. Whether the plugin can only be activated network wide.</code></pre>\n<p>Some users have issues with opening large files and manipulating the contents\nfor want is usually the first 1kiB or 2kiB. This function stops pulling in\nthe plugin contents when it has all of the required plugin data.</p>\n<p>The first 8kiB of the file will be pulled in and if the plugin data is not\nwithin that first 8kiB, then the plugin author should correct their plugin\nand move the plugin data headers to the top.</p>\n<p>The plugin file is assumed to have permissions to allow for scripts to read\nthe file. This is not checked however and the file is only opened for\nreading.</p>','get_plugin_data','Parse the plugin contents to retrieve plugin\'s metadata.','publish','open','open','','get_plugin_data','','','2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','',0,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/functions/get_plugin_data/',0,'wp-parser-function','',0),(2673,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','','_get_plugin_data_markup_translate','Sanitizes plugin data, optionally adds markup, optionally translates.','publish','open','open','','_get_plugin_data_markup_translate','','','2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','',0,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/functions/_get_plugin_data_markup_translate/',0,'wp-parser-function','',0),(2674,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','','get_plugin_files','Get a list of a plugin\'s files.','publish','open','open','','get_plugin_files','','','2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','',0,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/functions/get_plugin_files/',0,'wp-parser-function','',0),(2675,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','<p>WordPress only supports plugin files in the base plugins directory\n(wp-content/plugins) and in one directory above the plugins directory\n(wp-content/plugins/my-plugin). The file it looks for has the plugin data and\nmust be found in those two locations. It is recommended that do keep your\nplugin files in directories.</p>\n<p>The file with the plugin data is the file that will be included and therefore\nneeds to have the main execution for the plugin. This does not mean\neverything must be contained in the file and it is recommended that the file\nbe split for maintainability. Keep everything in one file for extreme\noptimization purposes.</p>','get_plugins','Check the plugins directory and retrieve all plugin files with plugin data.','publish','open','open','','get_plugins','','','2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','',0,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/functions/get_plugins/',0,'wp-parser-function','',0),(2676,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','<p>WordPress only includes mu-plugin files in the base mu-plugins directory (wp-content/mu-plugins).</p>','get_mu_plugins','Check the mu-plugins directory and retrieve all mu-plugin files with any plugin data.','publish','open','open','','get_mu_plugins','','','2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','',0,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/functions/get_mu_plugins/',0,'wp-parser-function','',0),(2677,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','','_sort_uname_callback','Callback to sort array by a \'Name\' key.','publish','open','open','','_sort_uname_callback','','','2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','',0,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/functions/_sort_uname_callback/',0,'wp-parser-function','',0),(2678,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','','get_dropins','Check the wp-content directory and retrieve all drop-ins with any plugin data.','publish','open','open','','get_dropins','','','2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','',0,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/functions/get_dropins/',0,'wp-parser-function','',0),(2679,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','<p>Includes Multisite drop-ins only when is_multisite()</p>','_get_dropins','Returns drop-ins that WordPress uses.','publish','open','open','','_get_dropins','','','2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','',0,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/functions/_get_dropins/',0,'wp-parser-function','',0),(2680,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','','is_plugin_active','Check whether the plugin is active by checking the active_plugins list.','publish','open','open','','is_plugin_active','','','2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','',0,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/functions/is_plugin_active/',0,'wp-parser-function','',0),(2681,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','<p>Reverse of is_plugin_active(). Used as a callback.</p>','is_plugin_inactive','Check whether the plugin is inactive.','publish','open','open','','is_plugin_inactive','','','2014-06-24 06:04:51','2014-06-24 06:04:51','',0,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/functions/is_plugin_inactive/',0,'wp-parser-function','',0),(2682,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:54','2014-06-24 06:04:54','','is_plugin_active_for_network','Check whether the plugin is active for the entire network.','publish','open','open','','is_plugin_active_for_network','','','2014-06-24 06:04:54','2014-06-24 06:04:54','',0,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/functions/is_plugin_active_for_network/',0,'wp-parser-function','',0),(2683,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:54','2014-06-24 06:04:54','<p>Checks for \"Site Wide Only: true\" for backwards compatibility.</p>','is_network_only_plugin','Checks for \"Network: true\" in the plugin header to see if this should\nbe activated only as a network wide plugin. The plugin would also work\nwhen Multisite is not enabled.','publish','open','open','','is_network_only_plugin','','','2014-06-24 06:04:54','2014-06-24 06:04:54','',0,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/functions/is_network_only_plugin/',0,'wp-parser-function','',0),(2684,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:54','2014-06-24 06:04:54','<p>A plugin that is already activated will not attempt to be activated again.</p>\n<p>The way it works is by setting the redirection to the error before trying to\ninclude the plugin file. If the plugin fails, then the redirection will not\nbe overwritten with the success message. Also, the options will not be\nupdated and the activation hook will not be called on plugin error.</p>\n<p>It should be noted that in no way the below code will actually prevent errors\nwithin the file. The code should not be used elsewhere to replicate the\n\"sandbox\", which uses redirection to work.\n{@source 13 1}</p>\n<p>If any errors are found or text is outputted, then it will be captured to\nensure that the success redirection will update the error redirection.</p>','activate_plugin','Attempts activation of plugin in a \"sandbox\" and redirects on success.','publish','open','open','','activate_plugin','','','2014-06-24 06:18:16','2014-06-24 06:18:16','',0,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/functions/activate_plugin/',0,'wp-parser-function','',0),(2685,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:54','2014-06-24 06:04:54','<p>If a plugin is silently activated (such as during an update),\nthis hook does not fire.</p>','\'activate_plugin\'','Fires before a plugin is activated.','publish','open','open','','activate_plugin','','','2014-06-24 06:04:54','2014-06-24 06:04:54','',2684,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/hooks/activate_plugin/',0,'wp-parser-hook','',0),(2686,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:54','2014-06-24 06:04:54','<p>This hook is the \"deactivation\" hook used internally by\nregister_deactivation_hook(). The dynamic portion of the\nhook name, $plugin. refers to the plugin basename.</p>\n<p>If a plugin is silently activated (such as during an update),\nthis hook does not fire.</p>','\'activate_\' . $plugin','Fires as a specific plugin is being deactivated.','publish','open','open','','activate_-plugin','','','2014-06-24 06:04:54','2014-06-24 06:04:54','',2684,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/hooks/activate_-plugin/',0,'wp-parser-hook','',0),(2687,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:54','2014-06-24 06:04:54','<p>If a plugin is silently activated (such as during an update),\nthis hook does not fire.</p>','\'activated_plugin\'','Fires after a plugin has been activated.','publish','open','open','','activated_plugin','','','2014-06-24 06:04:54','2014-06-24 06:04:54','',2684,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/hooks/activated_plugin/',0,'wp-parser-hook','',0),(2688,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:54','2014-06-24 06:04:54','<p>The deactivation hook is disabled by the plugin upgrader by using the $silent\nparameter.</p>','deactivate_plugins','Deactivate a single plugin or multiple plugins.','publish','open','open','','deactivate_plugins','','','2014-06-24 06:04:54','2014-06-24 06:04:54','',0,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/reference/functions/deactivate_plugins/',0,'wp-parser-function','',0),(2689,1,'2014-06-24 06:04:54','2014-06-24 06:04:54','<p>If a plugin is silently deactivated (such as during an update),\nthis hook does not fire.</p>','\'deactivate_plugin\'','Fires before a plugin is deactivated.','publish','open','open','','deac