wordpress.dev/954-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3645,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','','File_Upload_Upgrader','Upgrade Skin helper for File uploads. This class handles the upload process and passes it as if it\'s a local file to the Upgrade/Installer functions.','inherit','open','open','','955-revision-v1','','','2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','',955,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/955-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3646,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','','File_Upload_Upgrader::__construct','','inherit','open','open','','956-revision-v1','','','2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','',956,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/956-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3647,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','','File_Upload_Upgrader::cleanup','','inherit','open','open','','957-revision-v1','','','2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','',957,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/957-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3648,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','','WP_Automatic_Updater','The WordPress automatic background updater.','inherit','open','open','','958-revision-v1','','','2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','',958,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/958-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3649,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','','WP_Automatic_Updater::is_disabled','Whether the entire automatic updater is disabled.','inherit','open','open','','959-revision-v1','','','2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','',959,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/959-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3650,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','<p>There are more fine-grained filters and controls for selective disabling.\nThis filter parallels the AUTOMATIC_UPDATER_DISABLED constant in name.</p>\n<p>This also disables update notification emails. That may change in the future.</p>','\'automatic_updater_disabled\'','Filter whether to entirely disable background updates.','inherit','open','open','','960-revision-v1','','','2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','',960,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/960-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3651,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','<p>Checks for Subversion, Git, Mercurial, and Bazaar. It recursively looks up the\nfilesystem to the top of the drive, erring on the side of detecting a VCS\ncheckout somewhere.</p>\n<p>ABSPATH is always checked in addition to whatever $context is (which may be the\nwp-content directory, for example). The underlying assumption is that if you are\nusing version control <em>anywhere</em>, then you should be making decisions for\nhow things get updated.</p>','WP_Automatic_Updater::is_vcs_checkout','Check for version control checkouts.','inherit','open','open','','961-revision-v1','','','2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','',961,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/961-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3652,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','','\'automatic_updates_is_vcs_checkout\'','Filter whether the automatic updater should consider a filesystem\nlocation to be potentially managed by a version control system.','inherit','open','open','','962-revision-v1','','','2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','',962,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/962-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3653,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','','WP_Automatic_Updater::should_update','Tests to see if we can and should update a specific item.','inherit','open','open','','963-revision-v1','','','2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','',963,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/963-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3654,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','<p>The dynamic portion of the hook name, $type, refers to the type of update\nbeing checked. Can be \'core\', \'theme\', \'plugin\', or \'translation\'.</p>\n<p>Generally speaking, plugins, themes, and major core versions are not updated\nby default, while translations and minor and development versions for core\nare updated by default.</p>\n<p>See the allow_dev_auto_core_updates, allow_minor_auto_core_updates, and\nallow_major_auto_core_updates filters for a more straightforward way to\nadjust core updates.</p>','\'auto_update_\' . $type','Filter whether to automatically update core, a plugin, a theme, or a language.','inherit','open','open','','964-revision-v1','','','2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','',964,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/964-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3655,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','','WP_Automatic_Updater::send_core_update_notification_email','Notifies an administrator of a core update.','inherit','open','open','','965-revision-v1','','','2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','',965,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/965-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3656,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','<p>By default, administrators are notified when the update offer received\nfrom WordPress.org sets a particular flag. This allows some discretion\nin if and when to notify.</p>\n<p>This filter is only evaluated once per release. If the same email address\nwas already notified of the same new version, WordPress won\'t repeatedly\nemail the administrator.</p>\n<p>This filter is also used on about.php to check if a plugin has disabled\nthese notifications.</p>','\'send_core_update_notification_email\'','Filter whether to notify the site administrator of a new core update.','inherit','open','open','','966-revision-v1','','','2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','',966,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/966-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3657,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','','WP_Automatic_Updater::update','Update an item, if appropriate.','inherit','open','open','','967-revision-v1','','','2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','',967,'http://developer.wordpress.dev/967-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3658,1,'2014-06-24 05:46:49','2014-06-24 05:46:49','','WP_Automatic_Updater::run','Kicks off the